Te Puia Springs is a village on the east coast of the North Island of New Zealand, located 103 km north of Gisborne  Its population is estimated to be between 300 and 400 people. The village has a hospital and one shop. It has natural springs flowing throughout it, from hills in the NgƒÅti Porou area. The local people like to bathe in these springs, claiming that they have healing properties.
